# These users are automatically requested for review on PRs
# that modify files matching the patterns below.
#
# Order matters — last match wins.
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  SECONDARY-REVIEWER PLACEHOLDERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The repo has a single maintainer today. The commented-out
# lines below anticipate team growth and encode an *intent* for
# separation of duties on security-critical surfaces. As the
# team grows:
#
#   1. Replace `<security-team-member>` with an active
#      @username who owns security review (SAML, OIDC,
#      break-glass, audit, RBAC).
#   2. Replace `<platform-team-member>` with the platform /
#      infrastructure reviewer (controller, K8s, agent, EC2).
#   3. Uncomment the line and delete the placeholder token.
#   4. Cross-review the permission sets on sensitive paths
#      (two reviewers required for security-critical diffs —
#      configured via GitHub branch protection, not here).
#
